336  // --- read a table
337 // inline double readWaveTable(double readIndex, const double* currentWaveTable, unsigned int _tableLength)
338  inline double readWaveTable(double readIndex, void* currentWaveTable, uint32_t tableType, unsigned int _tableLength)
339  {
340  // --- two samples from table
341  double wtData[2] = { 0.0, 0.0 };
342 
343  // --- get INT part
344  int intReadIndex = abs((int)readIndex);
345 
346  // --- get FRAC part
347  double fractionalPart = readIndex - intReadIndex;
348 
349  // --- setup second index for interpolation; wrap the buffer if needed
350  int intReadIndexNext = intReadIndex + 1 > _tableLength - 1 ? 0 : intReadIndex + 1;
351 
352  if (tableType == 0) // decimal
353  {
354  wtData[0] = ((const double*)currentWaveTable)[intReadIndex];
355  wtData[1] = ((const double*)currentWaveTable)[intReadIndexNext];
356  }
357  if (tableType == 1) // hex
358  {
359  wtData[0] = uint64ToDouble(((const uint64_t*)currentWaveTable)[intReadIndex]);
360  wtData[1] = uint64ToDouble(((const uint64_t*)currentWaveTable)[intReadIndexNext]);
361  }
362 
363  // --- interpolate the output
364  double output = doLinearInterpolation(0.0, 1.0, wtData[0], wtData[1], fractionalPart);
365 
366  return output;
367  }
